        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 1:57PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Twin Lakes, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Tuolumne County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
